data.name: Grilled Balsamic Glazed Chicken
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy grilled chicken marinated in a rich balsamic glaze, served with sautéed seasonal vegetables.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix balsamic vinegar, honey, olive oil, minced garlic, salt, and black pepper to create the marinade.
Add the chicken breasts to the marinade and let them soak for at least 15 minutes.
Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked and juices run clear.
While chicken is grilling, sauté assorted seasonal vegetables in a pan with a drizzle of olive oil until tender.
Serve the grilled chicken on a plate with sautéed vegetables on the side, drizzled with any remaining balsamic glaze.
data.detailedName: Grilled Balsamic Glazed Chicken with Seasonal Vegetables
